      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "CLAUDYS HERO (9) put the writing on the wall when beaten just head here two back before leading to score by 6.7m at Bendigo last week. Draws on the back row this time but is going well enough to overcome that and score again. HOWDY MATE (8) was one of the leading juveniles of last season, his deeds including a Nutrien Classic win and Group 1 seconds in both the Vicbred Super Series and Breeders Crown finals. Readied with a trial placing and owns a good record at this circuit and distance. Draws for a trail and could make a winning return. COCONUT MICKEY (3) has recorded a win and a second the last two times he has raced here. Draws to be competitive again. MAJESTIC TOOTH (5) draws lower than in her brave effort last start when she raced parked but boxed on for second. ACOOL INVESTMENT (2) won well from a wider barrier last start.",
